The Katsina State Independent Electoral Commission (KTSIEC) has announced 11 April 2022 as the date for the Local Government Election in the state. Ibrahim Bako, the Chairman of KTSIEC, made the disclosure on Tuesday while addressing journalists at the commission. “It is my pleasure to officially announce that we have slated Monday 11th April 2022 to conduct the Local Government Councils Election in the State,” Bako said. The KTSIEC Chairman, however, noted that the announcement is with effect from 11th January to 11th April 2022 giving ninety days (90) notice in compliance with the Electoral Act 2010 as amended.” Bako advised stakeholders to comply and adhere strictly to the laws and guidelines governing the conduct of the Local Government Council in the state. He also noted that the “guidelines and timetable for the elections will be distributed to all and sundry in due cause.”